data.value:
You're here in the second tab of the client. The first tab, called "Routes calculator", has been created in order to help the user to get routes between his favorites stations, that he can select by entering the city he's living in.
Then, by entering the final address, the client will show him the best pedestrian and bicycle road from the selected station, and the final destination, using VLib.
If you have any questions, suggestions, or bug to report, feel free to send it to

data.name: label5.Text
data.value:
This program has been coded by Kevin VALERIO, for a Web Service / Service-Oriented Computing course, presented by Jean-Yves Tigli, teacher at Polytech Nice.
It uses a own-coded SOAP server, using an home-made JCDecaux library. This SOAP client use the SOAP server to get informations and datas, such as cache methods, functions...
It also uses the Xylos C# theme.
